#LePoulain is a great brunch place located close to Seocho station exits 3 and 4. It advertises as a bakery and cafe, but I stopped by to try their brunch menu. As soon as I saw #quiche, I knew what I was ordering. I haven't had quiche in ages, and this was advertised as spinach and tomato (main picture above). I was not disappointed. It came with delicious and soft bread, with a side of olive oil and basaltic vinegar, salad with shrimp, and of course, pickled radish. My friend order the daily brunch (pictured at the top of the photo), and it came with a mild but good soup. I also ended up buying two sets of chocolate chip with nuts cookies they had at their counter for my friends. Those were worth it. I dont normally like nuts, but the cookie looked and tasted like thick hearty cookies Ive had in the states. Definitely go for a great brunch place. Perfect for Saturdays if youre in the area or want to try a decent quiche.#ܷ #ʿ 3,4 ⱸƯ ʱ 1540-5Le Poulain 1540-5, Seocho-dong, Seocho-gu, #Seoul, #Korea
